 <center><h2>Ornate Shaman PoP Armors</h2></a><br><br>Each piece of this armor requires an ornate pattern, which is a rare drop in pre-elemental planes.<br><br>The quest part is pretty much a triviality, and the patterns are sold like regular armor pieces, but to transform an ornate chain pattern into some armor, give 'Bor Warhammer' in the Plane of Tranquility 500pp to get an emblem and a container, then combine the pattern, emblem and 1 to 3 metal rings (depending on piece) in the containter to get your armor. Metal rings are quite cheap in most bazaars, but if you want to make one, get a 220+ skill smith to combine a brick of ethereal energy and an ethereal temper.<br><br>Here are the rewards:<br><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=20077" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=11273" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=13569" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=15773" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=9829" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=16801" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><iframe src="http://www.eqshaman.com/itemstat1.php?id=11518" width="420" height="220" scrolling="no" frameborder="0"></iframe><br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?zone=159'>Plane of Tranquility (PoTr) mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=159'>Plane of Tranquility (PoTr) quest list</a><br><br><u>Comments/Feedback:</u><br><br><i><b>Kyofu - Saryrn</b> says:</i><br><br>In my personal opinion of comparing both the Ornate and EF armours (1492 points - highest chain in LDoN). They both have good stats.  The LDoN has more over all AC / HPs and comparable stats (but what shaman cares about stats =)...The noticiable different is the Effects / clickys on the Ornate.  I personally would Use 2x Bracer for FT4..unless you are already max FT.  Other than the clickys, the LDoN armour is better without Augs...not to mention adding augs to them (all of the ornate affects can be added to ldon armour besides saryrns venom / greater imobilize) - Personally, i say LDoN + nice augs is the way to go<br><br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br><br>well i tryin both myself i got bout 900 points in EF now and also killing just in BoT for some ornate junks. so that what i doin so whichever comes first i be happy :).<br><br><br><i><b>Phunnel - Rallos</b> says:</i><br><br>Ok i sound like a noob...but when can i get the ornate items?<br><br><br><i><b>Tormidon - BB</b> says:</i><br><br>Ok thanks for the tip<br><br><br><i><b>Tormidon - BB</b> says:</i><br><br>These armor pieces are nice, but with LDoN you can get similar stats on them for free from the Adventure Merchants...I am still deciding whether to sink the plat into these items, or to grind out Adventure Points to buy some LDoN armor<br><br><br><i><b>Kyofu - Saryrn</b> says:</i><br><br>In my personal opinion of comparing both the Ornate and EF armours (1492 points - highest chain in LDoN). They both have good stats.  The LDoN has more over all AC / HPs and comparable stats (but what shaman cares about stats =)...The noticiable different is the Effects / clickys on the Ornate.  I personally would Use 2x Bracer for FT4..unless you are already max FT.  Other than the clickys, the LDoN armour is better without Augs...