ether hehe).
<br><br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br><br>Ldon = better gear, droped augs, some droped items from named and lower exp / BoT great AA exp crappy drops. Yeah I would say Ldon for gear will take u less time and much saved PP. Most only take 25 min per on normal a little longer on hard <br><br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br><br>Ldon = much more exciting then sitting in bot, sorry ill take the ldon ef armor over sittin in bot all day long,hoping to get a lucky roll.)<br><br><br><i><b>Xilkoril</b> says:</i><br><br>Kk,  hears the deal IMO, if ur like me and ur usally bone dry pp wise becuse you are trying to get spells, go with EF LDoN, BUT there are the people that can afford 70k+ for them, GO FOR IT!! get the ornate. 
